set up venv

-create git ignore and add the following from
https://djangowaves.com/tips-tricks/gitignore-for-a-django-project/#:~:text=If%20you%20are%20using%20Git,has%20access%20to%20your%20code.

-create virt env
python3 -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\activate

-create requirements.txt

-create dockerfile

-create docker-compose.yml

create directory called app

pip install django

-from within the app dir run this command
django-admin startproject app .

pip install django-framework
pip3 install djangorestframework

make sure manage.py is in the top app dir 

-run the following:
docker-compose build
docker-compose up


